name: AI-PredictiveMaintenanceSystem
description: The AI-PMS Microservice uses AI to predict aircraft system failures before they occur, optimizing maintenance and enhancing safety. This modular microservice integrates with fleet management systems, providing real-time predictions and automated alerts for preventive maintenance interventions.

name: SimpleMicroservicesEcommereceSystem
description: Dive into the world of Spring Boot microservices with this hands-on project, which implements robust microservice communication with Feign, graceful failure handling with Hystrix, and efficient load balancing with Ribbon.

name: microservices
description: This project is where I'm applying what I've learned from the Microservices and Distributed Systems  course by Amigoscode. I'm using Spring Boot to build a system with microservices architecture, incorporating tools and concepts like Kubernetes, RabbitMQ, Kafka, and API Gateway security.

name: miniPastebin
description: pastebin microservices system for made for learning lgtm stack

name: service-boundary-analysis
description: Automating Domain-Based Microservices Conversion fromMonolithic Systems through Service Call Analysis

name: event-ticketing-system
description: Event Ticketing System with Email Notifications - A Node.js backend application for managing event ticket sales, including user registration, event management, and ticket booking, with a microservice for email notifications using BullMQ. Built with TypeScript and PostgreSQL.

name: Developpement-d-une-architecture-micro-service
description: This project is an e-commerce application built using a microservices architecture. It leverages Spring Boot and Spring Cloud to implement a scalable, decoupled system with dedicated services for billing, customer management, inventory, and more. The design includes centralized configuration, service discovery, and an API gateway.

name: banking-account-app
description: This repository contains a banking account application developed using Spring Boot with a microservices architecture. The application leverages Spring Cloud to implement distributed systems principles, ensuring scalability, resilience, and efficient inter-service communication.
